     <p><strong><p>Jens Andermann, Gabriel Gorgi and Victoria Saramago (eds.),<em> Handbook of Latin American Environmental Aesthetics</em>, De Gruyter, 2023, 493pp., $240.00 (hbk) ISBN 9783110775877.</p></strong></p>
     <p><strong>Reviewed by Omar Rivera, Texas A&amp;M University</strong></p>
     <p>TheÂ <em>Handbook for Latin American Environmental Aesthetics</em> is an essential contribution to a number of fields across the humanities and social sciences and shows the relevance of an emergent field for scholars studying literary theory, art history, decolonial theory, women of color feminisms, indigenous studies, environmental studies, and Latin American studies, among other interdisciplinary areas. The <em>Handbook</em> not only provides a reference for research in Latin American environmental aesthetics but also opens up a variety of extended horizons for future investigation in terms of the growing theoretical purview of this area of research, a wide array of artists and critical resources, and a nuanced articulation of relevant aesthetic and philosophical lineages.</p> <p>The reader will experience not so much the dry explanation of a field but the...
